
Please also update this doc-string, thanks! (And can you check if there are remaining occurrences of `prod_map` in mathlib?)
Can you revert the formatting changes, please?
optional: does `exact hx.prodMk hy` also work?
You're doing this because of the long line limit, right? Can you re-use the variable `f` or add a line-break (berhaps before `g`) instead?

Note that these lemmas are named different from the corresponding injectivity lemmas: #naming says
> An injectivity lemma that uses "left" or "right" should refer to the argument that "changes". For example, a lemma with the statement a - b = a - c â†” b = c could be called sub_right_inj.
Such a statement is not made here - so changing this would be good in a follow-up. Do you think we should change this, though? (Happy to start a discussion on zulip.)
Same question about line breaking
